# Personal AI Assistance — a brain, not an app. Information is never ignored here;
# only two categories stay out of git.

# 1. SECRETS — never commit credentials.
.env
.env.*
*.pem
*.key
*_token
03-rai/skills/news-digest/twscrape.db

# 2. MACHINE DROPPINGS + DERIVED STATE — regenerated, carry zero information.
__pycache__/
*.pyc
.DS_Store
.venv/
node_modules/

# ChromaDB vector store: a large binary REBUILT from your source memory + the
# pending queue. Keep it local and let each machine regenerate it (it was the #1
# source of git bloat). The information lives in your memory, not here.
03-rai/semantic-memory/chromadb/

# ── Going PUBLIC with your own fork? ───────────────────────────────────────────
# Your real life (02-ana/) and accumulated memory (03-rai/memory/) are PRIVATE.
# In a private vault you WANT them tracked. If you publish your vault publicly,
# uncomment the two lines below to keep your personal content out of history:
# 02-ana/
# 03-rai/memory/
